    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 21 with a clear offensive focus on our left-handed power and speed threats. **Kyle Schwarber** (77.03) and **Trea Turner** (75.86) lead the charge today, both benefiting significantly from favorable winds and matchup-specific platoon dynamics against the opposing lefties. **Schwarber** remains an elite volatility play given his .402 xwOBA, while **Turner**\u2019s dual-threat profile provides essential stability for our SB target despite the 40% hold rate from the opposing catcher. Meanwhile, **Kazuma Okamoto** (65.57) and **Caleb Durbin** (65.24) offer excellent value against weak starters; **Okamoto** is poised to exploit the wind out, and **Durbin** remains our most efficient play against a high-xERA arm like Gil, notwithstanding a minor penalty for his spot in the lower third of the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s board was excluding **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (42.58) from the outfield rotation. While his speed and platoon profile are attractive, his projected efficiency fell just short of our starters; the optimizer ultimately favored the higher-floor matchups of **Victor Scott II** and **Carson Benge** given the specific SP skill sets they are facing today. We are monitoring the weather in the **Hyeseong Kim** game, as a 42% rain risk creates a volatile floor for his 57.15 score. Elsewhere, we continue to carry **Christian Yelich** on the IL while **Colt Keith** and **Zac Veen** remain stashed as we await roster adjustments, keeping a close eye on the development of depth options like **Lars Nootbaar**, **Luke Raley**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, and **Luis Pena** to ensure our 5x5 categories remain covered throughout the week.",
